This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with superpixel-based object recognition and tracking applications. It may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it involves shape regularity and contour smoothness. Additionally, it could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) as it discusses noise and scale robustness. The paper's focus on proposing a new metric for evaluating superpixel methods suggests it could also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
